1
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:35,539
Winter Begonia

2
00:01:35,539 --> 00:01:38,020
Episode 28

3
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,390
Mr. Cheng has photos of me?

4
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:45,470
Are you blind?

5
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,710
This is my mother.

6
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,590
She looked great.

7
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:59,470
She used to sing operas as well.

8
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,710
She also performed the best as

9
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,790
Lady Yang.

10
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:10,229
I’ve been looking for her for more than a decade.

11
00:02:11,030 --> 00:02:12,550
I hadn’t been able to find anything.

12
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,150
I finally found something.

13
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,829
But then it was burnt.

14
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,310
Letters…

15
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,630
If there’s one letter,

16
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,590
there must be more.

17
00:02:25,510 --> 00:02:27,510
If she was able to

18
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,390
find your address,

19
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,990
she will come to you one day.

20
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:33,230
Just be patient.

21
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:36,790
What’s your plan now?

22
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:41,150
One step at a time.

23
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:44,150
I’m all on my own now.

24
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,110
I’ve got nothing to lose.

25
00:02:46,150 --> 00:02:47,790
What do you mean nothing?

26
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,110
You’ve got me.

27
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:50,829
Shuiyun Theatre will take care of you.

28
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,110
I am very high-maintenance.

29
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:56,110
I only use

30
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,030
the best imported goods.

31
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,350
There’s also

32
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:01,310
a baby to feed.

33
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,590
How are you going to take care of us?

34
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:06,830
Taking care of you two is not a problem.

35
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:08,910
Shuiyun Theatre is a cash cow.

36
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,830
When the time comes,

37
00:03:11,140 --> 00:03:11,730
all you need to do,

38
00:03:11,820 --> 00:03:12,850
is to stand next to the cow,

39
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:15,370
and I will bring you all the money.

40
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:18,650
Terrific.

41
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:21,170
I chose the right person.

42
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:22,970
Now,

43
00:03:23,180 --> 00:03:24,210
take the water out.

44
00:03:24,579 --> 00:03:25,210
Go to bed.

45
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:32,170
Wait! The towel!

46
00:03:51,460 --> 00:04:03,920
♬ The moon ♬

47
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:15,870
♬ Gently rises over the island ♬

48
00:04:23,060 --> 00:04:24,250
Mom, why did you stop?

49
00:04:25,890 --> 00:04:27,170
You father is coming back soon.

50
00:04:28,060 --> 00:04:30,490
He doesn’t like me singing at home.

51
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:31,690
But I like it.

52
00:04:34,140 --> 00:04:35,170
Well then,

53
00:04:35,290 --> 00:04:37,090
I will secretly sing it for you.

54
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:38,130
Great!

55
00:04:53,430 --> 00:04:54,330
Harder.

56
00:04:54,620 --> 00:04:55,409
I can’t go any more, leader.

57
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:56,130
More! Higher!

58
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:58,130
You’re very stiff.

59
00:04:58,140 --> 00:04:59,850
I can’t anymore, leader.

60
00:05:01,820 --> 00:05:02,490
Leader…

61
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:05,090
I can’t… Leader…

62
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:06,290
Leader I’m going to die.

63
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,810
Stand up straight, all of you.

64
00:05:12,340 --> 00:05:13,370
Leader!

65
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:15,210
I can’t.

66
00:05:18,660 --> 00:05:19,970
Can’t do this, boss.

67
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:20,850
Higher up.

68
00:05:20,860 --> 00:05:21,330
I can’t…

69
00:05:22,540 --> 00:05:23,530
You’re very stiff…

70
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:24,970
Leader… Dying…

71
00:05:25,140 --> 00:05:26,730
I’m not dying.

72
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:28,490
I’m quite alright.

73
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:29,690
Leader, I can’t do this.

74
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:31,050
Try harder.

75
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:31,810
From the waist.

76
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:32,570
Higher.

77
00:05:37,060 --> 00:05:38,250
Higher. Try harder.

78
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:39,250
No I can’t!

79
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:40,490
Morning, Mr. Cheng.

80
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:41,490
I can’t…

81
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:44,360
Are you trying to train these people,

82
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:45,650
or kill them?

83
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:46,370
Yes…

84
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:47,230
No, no killing.

85
00:05:49,310 --> 00:05:50,130
Harder.

86
00:05:50,260 --> 00:05:51,570
Go easy on them.

87
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:53,690
If they want to make it,

88
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,810
you’ll have to cut them open,

89
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,490
crush their bones,

90
00:05:57,620 --> 00:05:59,130
and mold a new person

91
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:00,730
with their flesh.

92
00:06:01,140 --> 00:06:02,330
Everyone has to do it.

93
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:03,890
No exception.

94
00:06:04,980 --> 00:06:06,090
Do you want to make it?

95
00:06:07,260 --> 00:06:08,010
Yes!

96
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:10,650
Does everyone want to make it?

97
00:06:10,660 --> 00:06:12,010
Yes!

98
00:06:12,020 --> 00:06:13,570
Then suck it up!

99
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:17,250
After you make it, you’ll make that cash.

100
00:06:17,810 --> 00:06:18,690
Hold it.

101
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:21,690
Hold it. Higher up.

102
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:22,330
-Here you are.
-From your waist!

103
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:23,090
-More strength!
-Thank you.

104
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:26,210
Mr. Cheng,

105
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:27,290
are you not having breakfast with me?

106
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:32,650
No slacking!

107
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:35,850
From the waist, up!

108
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:40,900
Manager Fan is here.

109
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:42,690
What happened to your head?

110
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:43,370
Mr. Fan.

111
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:48,610
Brother…

112
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,810
When did you come back?

113
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:52,810
This noon.

114
00:06:57,940 --> 00:06:59,010
Did you sister do that to you?

115
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:00,750
Who else dares to hurt me

116
00:07:00,940 --> 00:07:02,330
other than her?

117
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:04,530
Brother,

118
00:07:04,740 --> 00:07:06,330
you saved me from such a big trouble,

119
00:07:06,980 --> 00:07:08,610
I can’t be a coward, right?

120
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:09,980
You deserved to be hit.

121
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:12,250
In fact, you need to be hit harder.

122
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:14,970
You should be hit to death.

123
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:18,570
Look at the mess you made.

124
00:07:20,850 --> 00:07:21,930
What did you sister say?

125
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:23,570
She didn’t say anything.

126
00:07:24,260 --> 00:07:25,090
She thought

127
00:07:25,340 --> 00:07:26,740
we did it together.

128
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:29,370
You know her.

129
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:30,600
How stubborn she can be…

130
00:07:32,060 --> 00:07:32,810
The more you talk about these things,

131
00:07:32,980 --> 00:07:34,370
the more she suspects.

132
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:37,280
Just let her figure out on her own.

133
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:39,440
What do we do?

134
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,010
What if she never figures out?

135
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,570
Are you going to stay here forever?

136
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:47,490
You also don’t like staying at home, do you?

137
00:07:50,060 --> 00:07:51,450
I finally get to stay out of the house.

138
00:07:52,420 --> 00:07:53,730
Let me be for a few days.

139
00:07:55,990 --> 00:07:57,060
Three of us going through all this,

140
00:07:57,340 --> 00:07:58,850
for one child.

141
00:07:59,659 --> 00:08:00,570
Whom else should this be for?

142
00:08:03,450 --> 00:08:04,250
For me!

143
00:08:04,310 --> 00:08:05,090
For me…

144
00:08:05,930 --> 00:08:06,650
Brother,

145
00:08:06,940 --> 00:08:08,250
you did the most of it.

146
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:12,370
Brother,

147
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:14,810
do they have a spare room here for you?

148
00:08:15,820 --> 00:08:16,530
Why don’t you

149
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:17,960
crush at my place?

150
00:08:19,220 --> 00:08:20,150
Your place?

151
00:08:20,430 --> 00:08:23,090
All those people. Such a mess.

152
00:08:23,620 --> 00:08:25,010
Not even as quiet as Shuiyun Theatre.

153
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:26,610
I’m not going anywhere.

154
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:28,050
I’ll stay here at the theatre.

155
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:31,570
Right,

156
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:34,090
Zeng Aiyu is leaving Peking tonight.

157
00:08:34,190 --> 00:08:35,210
You need to see her off.

158
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:43,250
I’m worried that she won’t see me.

159
00:08:45,540 --> 00:08:46,880
Such a coward.

160
00:08:47,780 --> 00:08:49,050
Leader is coming.

161
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:51,930
Where’s his kettle?

162
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:53,370
Anyone saw it?

163
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:04,890
I’ll deal with you later.

164
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:14,910
I’ll have to go out a for a bit.

165
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:15,950
Don’t forget

166
00:09:16,190 --> 00:09:16,870
to get some rest.

167
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:17,910
You have another show tonight.

168
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:33,750
Mr. Cheng.

169
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:53,290
Mr. Cheng.

170
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:54,370
You’re here.

171
00:09:56,980 --> 00:09:57,650
I apologize.

172
00:09:57,660 --> 00:09:59,890
I didn’t see anything.

173
00:10:04,820 --> 00:10:06,530
Just to let her have a little from her own mom.

174
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:09,130
She won’t get any

175
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,260
after this.

176
00:10:33,290 --> 00:10:33,930
All done.

177
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,330
You can turn around.

178
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:49,210
Are you really leaving Peking?

179
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:54,770
Tell me what happened with your family.

180
00:10:55,460 --> 00:10:56,690
I can help.

181
00:11:01,020 --> 00:11:01,690
Help me?

182
00:11:05,620 --> 00:11:06,450
You help me

183
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:08,850
and I can stay.

184
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:13,570
Then what?

185
00:11:20,170 --> 00:11:21,810
Are you going to marry me?

186
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:57,000
If you really want to be with the baby…

187
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,370
It’s better for her

188
00:12:00,020 --> 00:12:01,290
if she stays with you.

189
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:07,210
Fine.

190
00:12:09,060 --> 00:12:10,130
Give her to me.

191
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:12,890
I’ll treat her as my own daughter.

192
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:15,370
Don’t you worry.

193
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:17,210
Mr. Cheng.

194
00:12:18,620 --> 00:12:19,650
The luggage has been loaded.

195
00:12:21,730 --> 00:12:22,450
Got it.

196
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:28,850
Just to hold her a little longer.

197
00:12:32,820 --> 00:12:33,650
From now on,

198
00:12:37,420 --> 00:12:38,810
I can only think about her

199
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:43,050
for the rest of my life.

200
00:13:08,860 --> 00:13:10,370
It’s not too late to change your mind.

201
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:26,090
There there…

202
00:13:37,820 --> 00:13:39,290
This jade pedant

203
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:41,650
looks like a feather.

204
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:45,690
It’s a phoenix tail.

205
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:10,650
Mommy wanted to leave it to you

206
00:14:12,220 --> 00:14:13,090
as something to hold on to.

207
00:14:15,780 --> 00:14:16,930
But I need this jade

208
00:14:19,180 --> 00:14:20,410
for something else.

209
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:26,490
I can’t leave it to you.

210
00:14:29,420 --> 00:14:30,470
Child,

211
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:33,890
don’t blame me.

212
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:36,730
Since this is

213
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:39,690
a phenix tail.

214
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:42,090
I’ll just call the baby

215
00:14:43,140 --> 00:14:44,370
Fengwei (phenix tail).

216
00:14:45,980 --> 00:14:47,210
Something to hold on to.

217
00:14:48,090 --> 00:14:49,290
Fengwei…

218
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:56,810
Fengwei.

219
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:09,650
I think she likes it.

220
00:15:10,310 --> 00:15:11,290
There there baby.

221
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:15,810
Fengwei.

222
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:28,050
Thank you, Mr. Cheng.

223
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,770
Where is Fan Lian anyway?

224
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:39,170
That’s it.

225
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:40,340
No more waiting.

226
00:15:41,580 --> 00:15:43,370
Or I’ll miss my train.

227
00:16:05,060 --> 00:16:05,890
Mr. Ge,

228
00:16:06,980 --> 00:16:07,730
thank you.

229
00:16:08,620 --> 00:16:10,290
Get her on the train safe.

230
00:16:10,930 --> 00:16:11,850
And go home.

231
00:16:12,340 --> 00:16:13,530
Don’t worry, Mr. Cheng.

232
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:35,450
Hurry.

233
00:16:36,580 --> 00:16:37,440
Hurry up!

234
00:16:40,090 --> 00:16:41,170
Faster!

235
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:04,140
(Peking Station)

236
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:08,380
(Exit)

237
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:35,580
What took you so long?

238
00:17:41,540 --> 00:17:42,730
I went to the train station.

239
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:44,810
Did you see her?

240
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:52,730
I know you’re not really married.

241
00:17:53,980 --> 00:17:55,410
But since she was pregnant,

242
00:17:56,290 --> 00:17:58,570
you’ve been very upset and indecisive.

243
00:17:59,610 --> 00:18:01,650
You don’t want to lose the baby nor the money.

244
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,530
No wonder she can’t respect you.

245
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:07,000
Arms out.

246
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:09,450
What?

247
00:18:10,020 --> 00:18:10,810
Arms out.

248
00:18:15,180 --> 00:18:15,890
Take her.

249
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:20,290
Okay…

250
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:21,730
Higher up.

251
00:18:22,780 --> 00:18:24,090
Hold her bottom.

252
00:18:26,930 --> 00:18:28,170
I’ll tidy up.

253
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:39,050
Brother,

254
00:18:39,540 --> 00:18:41,120
why… why is she crying?

255
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,290
She’s probably hungry.

256
00:18:43,450 --> 00:18:44,560
-There’s a bottle on the table.
-There there…

257
00:18:44,780 --> 00:18:45,540
Feed her some milk.

258
00:18:47,140 --> 00:18:48,480
Check the temperature with the back of your hand.

259
00:18:48,540 --> 00:18:49,330
Don’t burn her.

260
00:18:49,660 --> 00:18:50,690
A few drops are enough.

261
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:51,570
This?

262
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:52,650
Yes.

263
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:55,400
There there. It’s okay…

264
00:18:57,690 --> 00:18:58,610
It’s okay baby.

265
00:18:59,260 --> 00:19:00,170
There there.

266
00:19:00,180 --> 00:19:01,210
It’s okay honey.

267
00:19:04,930 --> 00:19:05,780
Where is the nanny?

268
00:19:05,940 --> 00:19:06,770
Where did she go?

269
00:19:07,060 --> 00:19:07,730
I let her go.

270
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:09,930
Why?

271
00:19:10,140 --> 00:19:11,450
Who is going to take care of the baby?

272
00:19:11,670 --> 00:19:12,910
She got trachoma.

273
00:19:13,460 --> 00:19:14,450
I don’t want her to give it to the baby.

274
00:19:14,460 --> 00:19:15,250
So I let her go.

275
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:17,850
It’s okay. It’s okay.

276
00:19:17,860 --> 00:19:19,610
Don’t cry, baby.

277
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:20,980
Brother,

278
00:19:20,990 --> 00:19:21,930
what were you thinking?

279
00:19:22,060 --> 00:19:23,970
It’s okay baby.

280
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:25,650
Just have some milk.

281
00:19:28,140 --> 00:19:29,050
Brother, brother…

282
00:19:29,660 --> 00:19:30,570
She’s still crying.

283
00:19:30,580 --> 00:19:32,260
She won’t stop.

284
00:19:34,220 --> 00:19:35,450
It’s okay…

285
00:19:35,460 --> 00:19:36,640
It’s fine. Don’t cry, baby.

286
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:37,770
Oh… It’s wet.

287
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:41,090
You need to change the diapers.

288
00:19:41,940 --> 00:19:42,450
What…

289
00:19:45,060 --> 00:19:46,570
I can’t do that.

290
00:19:46,580 --> 00:19:47,680
You’re her father.

291
00:19:47,690 --> 00:19:48,580
Where’s your responsibility?

292
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:52,010
Where is it?

293
00:19:52,220 --> 00:19:52,970
Where is it?

294
00:19:53,180 --> 00:19:54,210
Where is it?

295
00:19:55,940 --> 00:19:57,970
It takes time to build a relationship with her.

296
00:19:58,380 --> 00:19:59,490
You should do it…

297
00:20:00,420 --> 00:20:01,700
Brother, please.

298
00:20:01,820 --> 00:20:02,370
Here, give her to me.

299
00:20:03,460 --> 00:20:04,730
There, there.

300
00:20:10,220 --> 00:20:11,130
It’s okay.

301
00:20:11,140 --> 00:20:11,770
It’s okay baby.

302
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:13,250
There you go.

303
00:20:13,980 --> 00:20:14,730
Good girl.

304
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:16,490
I’ll change your diapers right away.

305
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,450
Bring me the baby powders.

306
00:20:23,810 --> 00:20:24,570
This is baby formula.

307
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:25,570
The other one.

308
00:20:29,340 --> 00:20:30,320
This.

309
00:20:30,610 --> 00:20:31,930
Oh that’s a lot!

310
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:33,170
Well done. Good girl.

311
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:36,610
There. Some baby powders.

312
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:38,970
Now you’ll feel all better.

313
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:41,010
Good girl.

314
00:20:41,630 --> 00:20:42,450
All done.

315
00:20:44,940 --> 00:20:45,730
Brother,

316
00:20:46,060 --> 00:20:47,330
I’m not even half as good as you are at this.

317
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:48,810
I feel that

318
00:20:49,990 --> 00:20:51,570
you’re her father.

319
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:52,450
Get out.

320
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:01,090
Brother,

321
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:02,410
let me ask you.

322
00:21:03,060 --> 00:21:05,690
Are you really leaving my sister?

323
00:21:08,420 --> 00:21:10,290
That’s not up to me.

324
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:12,690
What… What are you going to do?

325
00:21:13,170 --> 00:21:15,210
Who… Who is going to take care of this baby?

326
00:21:18,620 --> 00:21:20,050
Don’t look at me like that.

327
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:21,330
It’s not that I don’t want her.

328
00:21:21,660 --> 00:21:23,250
It’s just that all the uncles

329
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:25,570
will be mad at me if I take her back.

330
00:21:25,580 --> 00:21:27,050
She’s better off without you.

331
00:21:27,820 --> 00:21:29,370
I’ll take her back to the theatre.

332
00:21:29,660 --> 00:21:30,770
Shuiyun Theatre?

333
00:21:32,230 --> 00:21:34,170
Why don’t you just stay here?

334
00:21:34,220 --> 00:21:34,810
I don’t want to.

335
00:21:36,180 --> 00:21:37,890
Since I rented this place,

336
00:21:38,180 --> 00:21:40,280
so many bad things have happened.

337
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,520
The fengshui is probably wrong.

338
00:21:45,630 --> 00:21:47,150
Are you also superstitious?

339
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,370
I didn’t believe in these things.

340
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:52,450
But recently I feel like

341
00:21:53,230 --> 00:21:54,890
things are just a bit too odd to explain.

342
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:15,650
Wait,

343
00:22:34,490 --> 00:22:35,570
her hat is a bit off.

344
00:22:36,180 --> 00:22:37,210
I’ll fix it.

345
00:22:43,380 --> 00:22:44,130
Baby girl…

346
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:44,210
Sister,

347
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:48,210
do you know where my brother went

348
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:49,850
after moving out of here?

349
00:23:58,060 --> 00:23:59,490
Shuiyun Theatre!

350
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:02,290
He’s living in a theatre!

351
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:04,090
Let her be.

352
00:24:04,820 --> 00:24:06,970
He likes hanging out

353
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:08,010
with those show people.

354
00:24:08,220 --> 00:24:09,810
I can’t control him anyways, right?

355
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:13,190
You would’ve been furious

356
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:14,730
if this happened in the past.

357
00:24:15,410 --> 00:24:17,340
How are you so calm now?

358
00:24:22,220 --> 00:24:23,110
Are you really thinking about

359
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:24,410
leaving my brother?

360
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,550
This time,

361
00:24:27,780 --> 00:24:28,690
we both made mistakes.

362
00:24:28,820 --> 00:24:30,090
We’re both guilty.

363
00:24:31,620 --> 00:24:33,410
Neither of us will give in.

364
00:24:35,730 --> 00:24:37,100
Aren’t you afraid that

365
00:24:37,110 --> 00:24:39,280
my brother will betray you?

366
00:24:39,380 --> 00:24:41,330
Then divorce you and marry someone else?

367
00:24:43,620 --> 00:24:44,370
Sister,

368
00:24:45,020 --> 00:24:46,610
do you really think

369
00:24:46,620 --> 00:24:47,890
I’m just sitting at home, doing nothing?

370
00:24:49,100 --> 00:24:50,810
I’ve done my homework

371
00:24:50,820 --> 00:24:51,690
on that Zeng Aiyu.

372
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:55,680
A young and pretty social butterfly.

373
00:24:56,540 --> 00:24:59,050
Had Mr. Cheng and Fan Lian fooled.

374
00:25:00,660 --> 00:25:03,010
I have both Mr. Cheng’s check book

375
00:25:03,020 --> 00:25:04,090
and his stamp.

376
00:25:04,100 --> 00:25:05,450
He doesn’t have much cash with him.

377
00:25:06,050 --> 00:25:06,890
Will she still hang around

378
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:08,410
after he runs out of money?

379
00:25:09,660 --> 00:25:11,650
As long as I have the control over the money,

380
00:25:14,260 --> 00:25:16,450
he can’t go anywhere.

381
00:25:20,180 --> 00:25:21,290
All I need to do

382
00:25:21,510 --> 00:25:23,250
is to take care of this business.

383
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:26,610
When Cheng Fengtai gets a taste of being poor,

384
00:25:28,100 --> 00:25:29,970
when he finally sees what she really is,

385
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:32,090
he will be back.

386
00:25:33,770 --> 00:25:35,930
Hope he’ll find her mother back

387
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:37,810
by then.

388
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:41,610
I had indeed

389
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,850
underestimated you.

390
00:25:45,780 --> 00:25:47,370
You didn’t underestimate me.

391
00:25:47,850 --> 00:25:50,730
You only underestimated where I came from.

392
00:25:55,180 --> 00:25:55,970
You…

393
00:25:56,540 --> 00:25:58,050
You’re indeed

394
00:25:58,180 --> 00:25:59,730
very clever with your words!

395
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:05,760
Whose baby is this?

396
00:26:05,980 --> 00:26:07,010
So cute!

397
00:26:07,020 --> 00:26:07,850
My little daughter.

398
00:26:08,110 --> 00:26:08,650
Isn’t she adorable?

399
00:26:08,780 --> 00:26:09,990
-So adorable.
-So pretty.

400
00:26:10,010 --> 00:26:11,040
She really looks like you, Mr. Cheng!

401
00:26:11,050 --> 00:26:12,530
So pretty.

402
00:26:12,950 --> 00:26:13,720
Adorable.

403
00:26:14,060 --> 00:26:14,770
Indeed…

404
00:26:17,100 --> 00:26:18,050
What are you all doing here!

405
00:26:18,060 --> 00:26:18,650
So noisy.

406
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:20,050
-I’m trying to prepare for the show there.
-Leader.

407
00:26:20,340 --> 00:26:20,770
I…

408
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:22,690
What on earth is this?

409
00:26:25,460 --> 00:26:26,810
This is my little girl.

410
00:26:27,740 --> 00:26:29,410
Didn’t I tell you last time already?

411
00:26:31,380 --> 00:26:33,290
But you didn’t say you’d bring her here.

412
00:26:33,460 --> 00:26:35,090
Where else will I take her?

413
00:26:35,620 --> 00:26:36,730
Should I sleep on the street with her?

414
00:26:37,660 --> 00:26:38,930
I didn’t mean that.

415
00:26:39,420 --> 00:26:40,010
Mr. Cheng,

416
00:26:40,180 --> 00:26:41,010
don’t you know?

417
00:26:41,340 --> 00:26:42,180
Our leader

418
00:26:42,340 --> 00:26:43,170
is afraid of children.

419
00:26:43,460 --> 00:26:44,670
He finds them scary.

420
00:26:46,790 --> 00:26:48,330
What’s wrong with you this time?

421
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:51,770
Don’t you think it’s very scary when they cry?

422
00:26:51,900 --> 00:26:53,610
It sounds like when you’re walking alone

423
00:26:53,620 --> 00:26:54,730
in the middle of the night

424
00:26:54,980 --> 00:26:56,810
and you walk by the graveyard,

425
00:26:56,900 --> 00:26:57,850
and you hear the cats screaming…

426
00:26:58,850 --> 00:26:59,580
What are you talking about?

427
00:26:59,670 --> 00:27:01,050
What kind of metaphor is this?

428
00:27:02,820 --> 00:27:04,130
You’re just not familiar with them.

429
00:27:04,710 --> 00:27:05,850
All you need to do is hold them.

430
00:27:05,940 --> 00:27:06,450
Here, give it a go.

431
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:07,250
No, no, no.

432
00:27:07,300 --> 00:27:08,330
-Here. Come!
-Nope. No need.

433
00:27:08,370 --> 00:27:08,730
Mr. Cheng.

434
00:27:08,740 --> 00:27:09,860
-Come here.
-No! No way!

435
00:27:09,900 --> 00:27:13,010
-Help me!
-Just one second.

436
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:13,900
-One second.
-Leader!

437
00:27:13,940 --> 00:27:15,750
-Help!
-Just one second.

438
00:27:15,770 --> 00:27:17,190
-Mr. Cheng.
-Help me!

439
00:27:18,340 --> 00:27:19,530
Here. Don’t tease him.

440
00:27:19,540 --> 00:27:20,650
He really can’t stand babies.

441
00:27:20,820 --> 00:27:21,450
Come here.

442
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:22,670
Our leader doesn’t like you.

443
00:27:22,740 --> 00:27:23,970
I like you.

444
00:27:23,980 --> 00:27:25,050
Sister will sing for you, little girl.

445
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:25,770
Sister?

446
00:27:26,020 --> 00:27:27,380
Aren’t you even too old to be her aunt?

447
00:27:28,220 --> 00:27:28,810
Shut up.

448
00:27:28,820 --> 00:27:29,670
Dasheng!

449
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:32,990
What are you going to do

450
00:27:33,390 --> 00:27:34,890
when you have your own?

451
00:27:35,340 --> 00:27:36,170
I don’t want any.

452
00:27:37,300 --> 00:27:38,330
I don’t want kids.

453
00:27:39,140 --> 00:27:40,970
Then who will inherit

454
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:42,300
your legacy and skills

455
00:27:42,310 --> 00:27:43,050
from Shuiyun Theatre?

456
00:27:43,140 --> 00:27:43,970
I have Zhouzi.

457
00:27:44,980 --> 00:27:47,340
Zhouzi? Zhouzi?

458
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:48,690
Are you trying to take advantage of him?

459
00:27:48,940 --> 00:27:50,670
He’s not your child.

460
00:27:50,860 --> 00:27:52,530
I’m not my father’s biological child either.

461
00:27:52,860 --> 00:27:54,450
My brother was his biological son.

462
00:27:54,860 --> 00:27:56,570
But he couldn’t sing as well.

463
00:27:56,950 --> 00:27:58,370
He was a waste of food for my father.

464
00:27:58,740 --> 00:27:59,490
Get this,

465
00:27:59,730 --> 00:28:01,450
biological or not, it doesn’t matter.

466
00:28:01,860 --> 00:28:03,650
Sometimes your kids just don’t look like you.

467
00:28:04,340 --> 00:28:05,930
What kind of argument is this?

468
00:28:06,740 --> 00:28:08,130
If everyone thinks like this,

469
00:28:08,390 --> 00:28:09,650
we’d be going extinct already.

470
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:12,320
There are people like me running away from babies.

471
00:28:12,780 --> 00:28:15,250
There are those like you who can’t stop holding them.

472
00:28:15,700 --> 00:28:17,030
We keep it balanced.

473
00:28:17,270 --> 00:28:19,170
Human beings won’t be extinct.

474
00:28:20,380 --> 00:28:21,170
You simply

475
00:28:21,660 --> 00:28:22,850
don’t like children.

476
00:28:23,060 --> 00:28:24,890
You simply like children too much.

477
00:28:25,300 --> 00:28:26,930
You like them even when they’re not yours.

478
00:28:27,310 --> 00:28:28,970
You’d even pay for them.

479
00:28:29,140 --> 00:28:31,130
I should’ve just taken one home for you.

480
00:28:31,420 --> 00:28:32,770
It’ll save you a lot of money.

481
00:28:42,180 --> 00:28:43,250
Baby girl.

482
00:28:43,260 --> 00:28:44,290
-Well…
-She’s so cute.

483
00:28:46,020 --> 00:28:47,970
Does she have a name?

484
00:28:49,100 --> 00:28:50,180
Fengwei.

485
00:28:50,820 --> 00:28:52,910
Phenix tail.

486
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:56,530
Tail is not “Wei”

487
00:28:56,900 --> 00:28:57,490
Mr. Cheng,

488
00:28:57,980 --> 00:28:59,010
follow me,

489
00:28:59,540 --> 00:29:00,650
it’s “Yi”.

490
00:29:02,300 --> 00:29:03,210
Tail is pronounced as “Yi”.

491
00:29:03,220 --> 00:29:05,850
Fengyi… Yi…

492
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:06,770
Yi…

493
00:29:07,740 --> 00:29:08,610
Fengyi…

494
00:29:09,220 --> 00:29:09,770
That’s actually not bad.

495
00:29:09,820 --> 00:29:10,690
Sounds quite nice.

496
00:29:10,780 --> 00:29:11,330
Yes.

497
00:29:11,340 --> 00:29:13,370
We’ll call her Fengyi then.

498
00:29:13,740 --> 00:29:15,170
Fengyi!

499
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:16,130
Fengyi girl.

500
00:29:16,140 --> 00:29:16,690
What do you say?

501
00:29:16,780 --> 00:29:17,450
Fengyi?

502
00:29:17,670 --> 00:29:18,800
Cheng Fengtai.

503
00:29:19,020 --> 00:29:20,010
Cheng Fengyi.

504
00:29:20,460 --> 00:29:21,980
Same character.

505
00:29:22,380 --> 00:29:23,610
What a name.

506
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:27,530
Fengyi. Fengyi. Fengyi.

507
00:29:43,180 --> 00:29:43,970
Stop thinking about it.

508
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:44,520
Eat.

509
00:29:54,540 --> 00:29:56,920
Why do you think he left?

510
00:30:00,580 --> 00:30:03,050
Did I do something wrong?

511
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:05,090
Should we go talk to him?

512
00:30:09,820 --> 00:30:10,810
You did make a mistake

513
00:30:11,740 --> 00:30:14,130
by not talking to me earlier.

514
00:30:14,740 --> 00:30:16,930
Cheng Fengtai is a smart man.

515
00:30:17,220 --> 00:30:19,530
He wouldn’t take the baby to your cousin.

516
00:30:20,210 --> 00:30:22,210
He’s most likely just having a woman for fun.

517
00:30:22,740 --> 00:30:23,650
It’s already happened.

518
00:30:23,930 --> 00:30:25,050
Too late to talk to him now.

519
00:30:25,700 --> 00:30:26,650
For fun?

520
00:30:27,300 --> 00:30:27,610
This…

521
00:30:28,100 --> 00:30:29,650
Having an affair is not just for fun.

522
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:32,410
I can’t believe you just said that.

523
00:30:33,300 --> 00:30:35,530
If you’re helping her hide this today,

524
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:38,050
is he going to hide for your one day?

525
00:30:39,740 --> 00:30:41,600
This is his family matters.

526
00:30:41,940 --> 00:30:43,810
Why are you mad at me?

527
00:31:17,950 --> 00:31:24,200
♬ If I get to be selfish once ♬

528
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:30,280
♬ I’d like to shoulder your sins ♬

529
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:35,090
♬ So that you can smile ♬

530
00:31:36,980 --> 00:31:41,500
♬ So that we can cherish our time ♬

531
00:31:43,140 --> 00:31:48,980
♬ If I get to only cry once ♬

532
00:31:49,540 --> 00:31:54,270
♬ I wouldn’t be able to help ♬

533
00:31:55,700 --> 00:32:00,620
♬ Pretending nothing happened ♬

534
00:32:02,070 --> 00:32:07,050
♬ The flowers blossom from the dust ♬

535
00:32:11,740 --> 00:32:16,770
♬ I’m not afraid of our time together ♬

536
00:32:17,850 --> 00:32:23,170
♬ Let’s finish this drink and this show ♬

537
00:32:24,260 --> 00:32:30,410
♬ You understand my regrets without being told ♬

538
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:35,640
♬ You told me life was wonderful in my dream ♬

539
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:42,960
♬ Life is precious ♬

540
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:48,310
♬ We have to leave the sorrows behind ♬

541
00:32:49,870 --> 00:32:50,970
There there.

542
00:32:51,340 --> 00:32:51,910
It’s okay.

543
00:32:52,530 --> 00:32:53,870
It’s okay. Don’t cry.

544
00:32:54,220 --> 00:32:55,170
Are you hungry?

545
00:32:55,710 --> 00:32:57,550
♬ Look at the mountain ♬

546
00:32:57,580 --> 00:33:04,110
♬ Look at the dust on the satin ♬

547
00:33:04,220 --> 00:33:04,920
It’s okay.

548
00:33:05,460 --> 00:33:06,490
There, there.

549
00:33:06,530 --> 00:33:07,410
It’s okay.

550
00:33:16,050 --> 00:33:16,970
It’s okay.

551
00:33:17,100 --> 00:33:18,290
Don’t you cry.

552
00:33:19,300 --> 00:33:20,570
There, there.

553
00:33:20,580 --> 00:33:21,970
There, there.

554
00:33:26,620 --> 00:33:27,690
It’s okay.

555
00:33:27,900 --> 00:33:28,810
It’s okay.

556
00:33:29,140 --> 00:33:29,810
Cheng Fengtai,

557
00:33:29,940 --> 00:33:30,970
tell her to stop!

558
00:33:31,060 --> 00:33:32,050
We’re trying to sleep here!

559
00:33:32,140 --> 00:33:33,290
Will she listen to me?!

560
00:33:36,740 --> 00:33:37,970
It’s okay.

561
00:33:39,990 --> 00:33:44,920
♬ I pretend to muddle along as if nothing matters ♬

562
00:33:46,370 --> 00:33:52,110
♬ A bud blossoms from the dust ♬

563
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:54,170
You’re killing me.

564
00:33:54,740 --> 00:33:55,420
My son

565
00:33:55,780 --> 00:33:57,610
didn’t even worry me as much.

566
00:33:58,910 --> 00:34:04,090
♬ Let’s finish this drink and this show ♬

567
00:34:05,330 --> 00:34:11,440
♬ You understand my regrets without being told ♬

568
00:34:11,570 --> 00:34:16,960
♬ You told me life was wonderful in my dream ♬

569
00:34:19,429 --> 00:34:19,969
Stop.

570
00:34:21,260 --> 00:34:22,250
I’m busy taking care of the baby.

571
00:34:22,500 --> 00:34:23,210
I can’t take care of you as well.

572
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:25,449
I found a girl to take care of you.

573
00:34:25,940 --> 00:34:27,560
What did I do wrong?

574
00:34:28,130 --> 00:34:29,330
If you don’t like Chunxing,

575
00:34:29,340 --> 00:34:31,120
then find a “clean” one for yourself.

576
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:33,170
Why do you have to be so upset?

577
00:34:36,350 --> 00:34:37,520
You won’t understand.

578
00:34:38,510 --> 00:34:45,679
♬ Look at the dust on the satin ♬

579
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:50,290
When do you think

580
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:52,780
I get to go back

581
00:34:53,739 --> 00:34:55,600
and get you a little sister?

582
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:14,250
What’s happening here?

583
00:35:16,900 --> 00:35:18,010
What’s wrong with you?

584
00:35:18,820 --> 00:35:19,930
We didn’t do anything wrong.

585
00:35:21,660 --> 00:35:22,080
Wait,

586
00:35:23,300 --> 00:35:24,210
you’re making all this dust.

587
00:35:24,220 --> 00:35:25,210
We can’t practice in dust.

588
00:35:26,540 --> 00:35:27,210
Move along then.

589
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:28,050
Practice there.

590
00:35:28,500 --> 00:35:29,650
Can’t you see I’m airing the quilt

591
00:35:29,660 --> 00:35:30,620
for our money man?

592
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:32,330
He is the priority.

593
00:35:32,420 --> 00:35:33,450
More important than all of you.

594
00:35:34,540 --> 00:35:34,850
Wait a second.

595
00:35:34,860 --> 00:35:36,370
What’s the matter with you?

596
00:35:36,500 --> 00:35:38,010
Did Mr. Cheng do anything wrong?

597
00:35:38,460 --> 00:35:39,810
He is such a nice person.

598
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:41,490
He is nice.

599
00:35:42,610 --> 00:35:43,490
But that wife of him

600
00:35:43,700 --> 00:35:45,250
is basically blind.

601
00:35:45,300 --> 00:35:47,570
She’s so stupid.

602
00:35:49,780 --> 00:35:50,730
A word of advice,

603
00:35:50,860 --> 00:35:52,450
stay away from him.

604
00:35:53,330 --> 00:35:55,210
If she shows up here tomorrow,

605
00:35:55,540 --> 00:35:57,460
she will kill anyone

606
00:35:57,820 --> 00:35:59,810
who has talked to Mr. Cheng.

607
00:35:59,980 --> 00:36:00,610
All of you,

608
00:36:02,380 --> 00:36:04,170
will… will suffer.

609
00:36:04,530 --> 00:36:05,800
Wait. What does that mean?

610
00:36:05,830 --> 00:36:06,620
Whom are you talking about?

611
00:36:07,520 --> 00:36:08,010
Wait.

612
00:36:08,180 --> 00:36:08,730
Come here.

613
00:36:08,740 --> 00:36:09,370
Who?

614
00:36:09,500 --> 00:36:09,970
Whom?

615
00:36:09,980 --> 00:36:10,650
Talking about you.

616
00:36:10,660 --> 00:36:11,170
Shut up.

617
00:36:11,180 --> 00:36:12,650
I wasn’t talking about you.

618
00:36:14,660 --> 00:36:16,130
Whom?

619
00:36:17,420 --> 00:36:17,970
Tell me now.

620
00:36:17,980 --> 00:36:18,730
Leader.

621
00:36:18,940 --> 00:36:20,470
Leader! Leader! Leader.

622
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:25,290
♬ Cheng Fengtai, show yourself ♬

623
00:36:25,700 --> 00:36:27,490
♬ Here I come ♬

624
00:36:32,420 --> 00:36:33,450
♬ What can I do for you ♬

625
00:36:36,490 --> 00:36:36,850
Today

626
00:36:37,380 --> 00:36:39,050
I’m going to get us

627
00:36:39,500 --> 00:36:41,930
something really big, really fancy.

628
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:43,170
What is it?

629
00:36:43,180 --> 00:36:43,810
Yes, what is it?

630
00:36:43,820 --> 00:36:44,790
What thing?

631
00:36:45,060 --> 00:36:46,290
What are we getting?

632
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:47,050
Something big?

633
00:36:47,140 --> 00:36:47,920
Fancy?

634
00:36:47,980 --> 00:36:48,930
Listen up,

635
00:36:48,940 --> 00:36:49,890
listen.

636
00:36:49,900 --> 00:36:51,210
-Spill it.
-What is it?

637
00:36:51,430 --> 00:36:54,910
It’s got walls around it.

638
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:57,970
Inch away from the ground.

639
00:36:58,820 --> 00:36:59,810
Can you guess?

640
00:36:59,940 --> 00:37:01,390
-No idea.
-What is it?

641
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:02,610
What?

642
00:37:02,620 --> 00:37:03,400
I got it!

643
00:37:04,090 --> 00:37:05,050
A litter!

644
00:37:05,140 --> 00:37:05,810
That’s silly.

645
00:37:05,820 --> 00:37:06,990
Nonsense.

646
00:37:07,700 --> 00:37:08,930
I’m getting a car!

647
00:37:09,100 --> 00:37:11,370
A car? Car?

648
00:37:11,380 --> 00:37:12,730
A car for a theatre.

649
00:37:12,980 --> 00:37:14,530
That’s new.

650
00:37:14,540 --> 00:37:15,450
Right!

651
00:37:16,180 --> 00:37:17,090
Are we going to drive

652
00:37:17,100 --> 00:37:18,250
to our shows?

653
00:37:19,060 --> 00:37:19,810
I know!

654
00:37:19,820 --> 00:37:21,420
Don’t be silly.

655
00:37:21,810 --> 00:37:23,890
This car is for Mr. Cheng.

656
00:37:24,820 --> 00:37:26,050
For Mr. Cheng?

657
00:37:26,100 --> 00:37:27,010
Me?

658
00:37:28,060 --> 00:37:29,050
Did you say?

659
00:37:29,220 --> 00:37:30,200
You wanted a car.

660
00:37:30,470 --> 00:37:32,110
Those imported cars are not comfortable for you.

661
00:37:34,100 --> 00:37:35,530
I didn’t mean it.

662
00:37:36,180 --> 00:37:37,570
But I meant it.

663
00:37:39,700 --> 00:37:40,770
It’s just nonsense.

664
00:37:40,980 --> 00:37:42,050
I’m not taking the car.

665
00:37:43,820 --> 00:37:44,890
I’ve made a deal with them.

666
00:37:45,300 --> 00:37:47,010
You can buy me a meal.

667
00:37:47,300 --> 00:37:48,050
Cancel the car.

668
00:37:49,180 --> 00:37:49,810
This is too much.

669
00:37:51,500 --> 00:37:53,010
I’m want you to be happy.

670
00:37:55,060 --> 00:37:55,530
I’m happy.

671
00:37:56,580 --> 00:37:57,570
Very happy.

672
00:37:59,180 --> 00:38:01,170
I’ll order. You’ll pay.

673
00:38:02,650 --> 00:38:03,450
Right, Xiaolai,

674
00:38:04,060 --> 00:38:05,490
could you take care of Fengyi for me?

675
00:38:05,980 --> 00:38:07,090
The formula is in the room.

676
00:38:07,180 --> 00:38:07,890
On the table.

677
00:38:08,860 --> 00:38:09,410
Let’s go.

678
00:38:12,460 --> 00:38:14,210
That’s enough. Walk along.

679
00:38:14,340 --> 00:38:15,250
Let’s go. Let’s go.

680
00:38:15,260 --> 00:38:15,970
Back to practice.

681
00:38:15,980 --> 00:38:16,810
It’s about to rain.

682
00:38:17,540 --> 00:38:18,170
Mr. Cheng,

683
00:38:18,300 --> 00:38:19,010
take an umbrella with you!

684
00:38:20,460 --> 00:38:22,450
I’ll bring him the umbrella.

685
00:38:23,020 --> 00:38:23,530
He…

686
00:38:25,260 --> 00:38:28,090
A money man indeed.

687
00:38:28,100 --> 00:38:30,290
All these privileges.

688
00:38:30,620 --> 00:38:32,020
Being served all the time.

689
00:38:32,180 --> 00:38:32,970
Having people do things for him

690
00:38:33,990 --> 00:38:35,410
wherever he goes.

691
00:38:38,660 --> 00:38:39,650
Mr. Cheng,

692
00:38:39,860 --> 00:38:41,250
are you really not taking the car?

693
00:38:42,300 --> 00:38:43,450
I don’t need it.

694
00:38:44,180 --> 00:38:45,090
I’ll tell you what I want

695
00:38:45,260 --> 00:38:46,250
when I figure out.

696
00:38:48,900 --> 00:38:50,210
You really would spend that money for me?

697
00:38:50,940 --> 00:38:51,890
What are you saying?

698
00:38:52,340 --> 00:38:53,730
As long as I have a coin in my pocket,

699
00:38:53,740 --> 00:38:55,160
I’ll spend it for you.

700
00:38:56,060 --> 00:38:57,230
Don’t push! Don’t push!

701
00:38:57,260 --> 00:38:58,470
I have enough papers here.

702
00:38:58,860 --> 00:38:59,650
Here you go.

703
00:39:00,180 --> 00:39:00,970
Don’t push!

704
00:39:02,220 --> 00:39:03,450
Take this one.

705
00:39:04,500 --> 00:39:05,730
Are people going mad in Peking?

706
00:39:06,340 --> 00:39:08,170
They’re fighting for newspapers?

707
00:39:09,260 --> 00:39:10,570
They’re electing a leader at Opera Association.

708
00:39:10,980 --> 00:39:12,470
Peking Times is the sponsor.

709
00:39:12,540 --> 00:39:14,840
One paper means one vote.

710
00:39:15,140 --> 00:39:17,370
Whoever has more followers and money wins.

711
00:39:18,780 --> 00:39:20,330
Xue Qianshan knows how to make his money.

712
00:39:21,460 --> 00:39:22,130
-Mr. Shang.
-Don’t push.

713
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:24,230
I always hear about this leader of the Association.

714
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:25,810
What’s the big deal?

715
00:39:26,260 --> 00:39:27,030
Latest news!

716
00:39:27,060 --> 00:39:28,370
It’s got everyone in Peking

717
00:39:28,380 --> 00:39:30,210
so excited.

718
00:39:30,780 --> 00:39:32,170
The election of the leader

719
00:39:32,580 --> 00:39:33,970
happens once every 5 years.

720
00:39:34,140 --> 00:39:35,450
I haven’t been here long enough

721
00:39:35,460 --> 00:39:36,450
to see one before.

722
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:37,690
I heard that

723
00:39:37,700 --> 00:39:39,330
those who made it in the first round

724
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:41,170
will have to go through a second round.

725
00:39:41,500 --> 00:39:42,130
And then

726
00:39:42,140 --> 00:39:44,330
they will announce the result here at the Association.

727
00:39:44,380 --> 00:39:44,570
(The Opera Association)

728
00:39:44,570 --> 00:39:46,300
Winning the election
(The Opera Association)

729
00:39:46,300 --> 00:39:46,970
Winning the election

730
00:39:47,180 --> 00:39:48,410
is the biggest thing.

731
00:39:48,540 --> 00:39:49,770
The person gets to march the street.

732
00:39:49,900 --> 00:39:51,050
It’s really something.

733
00:39:53,620 --> 00:39:54,970
It does sound quite fun.

734
00:39:58,500 --> 00:40:00,210
Did your father win?

735
00:40:00,740 --> 00:40:01,410
My father.

736
00:40:02,710 --> 00:40:03,650
The first ever election he was the runner-up.

737
00:40:04,030 --> 00:40:06,310
Same with the second election.

738
00:40:07,810 --> 00:40:10,000
And then he left Peking.

739
00:40:10,300 --> 00:40:10,970
After that,

740
00:40:10,980 --> 00:40:12,570
he couldn’t stop thinking about

741
00:40:12,580 --> 00:40:13,530
this election.

742
00:40:13,540 --> 00:40:14,730
He kept talking about it

743
00:40:14,740 --> 00:40:15,810
all the time.

744
00:40:15,820 --> 00:40:16,890
I can recite his words now.

745
00:40:18,620 --> 00:40:19,650
Well then,

746
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:21,930
this is you representing your father.

747
00:40:23,100 --> 00:40:23,970
Too bad.

748
00:40:24,380 --> 00:40:25,930
I don’t have much money with me.

749
00:40:26,380 --> 00:40:27,530
Or you’ll definitely win.

750
00:40:27,540 --> 00:40:28,490
Shut up.

751
00:40:28,740 --> 00:40:30,170
I don’t need you to cheat for me.

752
00:40:31,860 --> 00:40:32,650
True.

753
00:40:33,220 --> 00:40:34,890
Mr. Shang is one famous performer.

754
00:40:35,180 --> 00:40:36,410
You’re already very capable.

755
00:40:42,540 --> 00:40:45,260
(The 5th Election of Peking)
(Shang Xirui winning first place)

756
00:40:45,260 --> 00:40:45,930
Be careful.
(The 5th Election of Peking)
(Shang Xirui winning first place)

757
00:40:45,930 --> 00:40:46,140
(The 5th Election of Peking)
(Shang Xirui winning first place)

758
00:40:46,140 --> 00:40:47,090
Don’t rush. Be careful.
(The 5th Election of Peking)
(Shang Xirui winning first place)

759
00:40:47,700 --> 00:40:48,830
-Okay.
-Slowly.

760
00:40:54,220 --> 00:40:55,370
Sir,

761
00:40:55,380 --> 00:40:56,290
welcome.

762
00:40:56,380 --> 00:40:57,050
Mr. Niu,

763
00:40:57,500 --> 00:40:59,610
the set up for this election

764
00:40:59,940 --> 00:41:01,530
is really fancy.

765
00:41:02,330 --> 00:41:03,250
Thanks to the sponsorship

766
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:04,760
from Peking Times.

767
00:41:05,850 --> 00:41:06,390
Take a look.

768
00:41:06,790 --> 00:41:08,450
How do you like the stage setup?

769
00:41:08,740 --> 00:41:09,450
Quite nice.

770
00:41:10,100 --> 00:41:12,770
It’ll look very good in the picture.

771
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:14,170
You guys,

772
00:41:14,940 --> 00:41:17,730
take photos of this stage and the setup.

773
00:41:18,140 --> 00:41:18,730
-Yes.
-Yes, sir.

774
00:41:22,900 --> 00:41:23,770
Sir,

775
00:41:24,020 --> 00:41:24,770
look,

776
00:41:24,780 --> 00:41:25,650
this is

777
00:41:25,830 --> 00:41:26,930
all I can do for you.

778
00:41:27,400 --> 00:41:28,210
Not it’s your turn

779
00:41:28,220 --> 00:41:29,850
to show your magic.

780
00:41:30,900 --> 00:41:32,170
8 writers

781
00:41:32,570 --> 00:41:34,130
and 60 articles.

782
00:41:34,660 --> 00:41:35,810
Is that enough?

783
00:41:36,140 --> 00:41:37,130
Sure. Certainly.

784
00:41:37,460 --> 00:41:39,000
Shang Xirui is here this year.

785
00:41:39,220 --> 00:41:39,810
You just wait.

786
00:41:39,820 --> 00:41:41,210
The money will go to you.

787
00:41:41,660 --> 00:41:42,690
How is that so?

788
00:41:42,830 --> 00:41:43,690
Think about it.

789
00:41:44,040 --> 00:41:45,050
Here at Peking,

790
00:41:45,060 --> 00:41:47,370
so many dramas have happened since Shang Xirui came.

791
00:41:47,780 --> 00:41:50,810
This election will be extra eventful.

792
00:41:51,140 --> 00:41:52,570
You just wait and see.

793
00:41:55,500 --> 00:41:56,730
At the end of the day,

794
00:41:56,740 --> 00:41:59,090
operas are about songs and music.

795
00:41:59,180 --> 00:42:01,690
All we need is audience and some popularity.

796
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:02,950
Don’t you agree?

797
00:42:03,180 --> 00:42:03,360
(Jiang’s Mansion)

798
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:06,510
Fried dough twist! Pancake!
(Jiang’s Mansion)

799
00:42:06,640 --> 00:42:07,790
Sir,

800
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:09,110
are you serious?

801
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:12,350
What’s wrong with your ears.

802
00:42:14,050 --> 00:42:15,830
I know my worth.

803
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:17,990
A few decades ago,

804
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:20,230
I might be elected.

805
00:42:21,040 --> 00:42:22,350
But now…

806
00:42:27,760 --> 00:42:28,670
Look at me.

807
00:42:30,870 --> 00:42:32,510
I haven’t performed for years.

808
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:35,550
Chen Renxiang left for Shanghai.

809
00:42:36,930 --> 00:42:38,150
Dengbao is not ambitious enough.

810
00:42:39,080 --> 00:42:40,470
I don’t think we have a successor

811
00:42:40,480 --> 00:42:42,270
here at Longchun Troupe.

812
00:42:43,120 --> 00:42:45,070
We have known each other for long enough.

813
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:48,190
Supporting you is better than anyone else.

814
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:55,590
I’ll give you a leak.

815
00:42:56,560 --> 00:42:58,950
Ning Jiulang is also participating this year.

816
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:03,430
How many years has it been?

817
00:43:03,580 --> 00:43:05,510
Don’t you want to compete with him again?

818
00:43:06,520 --> 00:43:08,030
Ning Jiulang…
